President Obama launched a national conversation on fatherhood and personal responsibility. He emphasized the importance of fathers in supporting families and sustaining communities. The President visited non-profit organizations dedicated to mentoring and supporting young men and held a town hall meeting on fatherhood. He highlighted the impact of responsible fathers and the challenges faced by children growing up without a father. President Obama issued a Father's Day proclamation and taped a public service announcement. The White House plans to continue these conversations with regional town hall forums to strengthen efforts in addressing fatherhood challenges.